<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10137i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10137i">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10137i"> 137(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> milk &amp; honey</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le culte de Mercure n&apos;avait rien de particulier, sinon qu&apos;on lui offrait les langues des victimes, embl&egrave;me de son &eacute;loquence. Par la m&ecirc;me raison, on lui offrait du lait et du miel. On lui immolait des veaux et des coqs. <font color="green">[The cult of Mercury had no specific features, except that one offered to him the tongues of sacrificial beasts, emblems of his eloquence. By the same reasoning he was offered milk and honey.]</font> <small> P. Commelin, <a name="NMGR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#NMGR"><cite title="source">Nouvelle Mythologie</cite></a> (1907) 60</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
